## 4. Annotation Dictionary

| Annotation | Location | Explanation |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **`@SpringBootApplication`** | `WeatherAppApplication.java` | Combines `@Configuration`, `@EnableAutoConfiguration` (sets up Tomcat), and `@ComponentScan` (finds Controllers/Services). |
| **`@RestController`** | `Controller.java` | Marks the class as a web controller returning Domain Objects (JSON). Combines `@Controller` and `@ResponseBody`. |
| **`@RequestMapping`** | `Controller.java` | Sets the base URI path (e.g., `/weather`). Methods inside are relative to this path. |
| **`@GetMapping`** | `Controller.java` | Maps HTTP GET requests to a specific method for fetching data. |
| **`@Autowired`** | `Controller.java` | Triggers Dependency Injection to plug in a managed bean (e.g., `WeatherService`). |
| **`@PathVariable`** | `Controller.java` | Binds a URL placeholder (e.g., `/Pune`) to a Java argument. Used for identifying specific resources. |
| **`@RequestParam`** | `Controller.java` | Binds a query parameter (e.g., `?days=3`) to an argument. Used for filtering or configuration. |
| **`@Service`** | `WeatherService.java` | Specialization of `@Component`. Marks the class as holding business logic for semantic readability. |
| **`@JsonPropertyOrder`** | `WeatherForCast.java` | Instructs the Jackson serializer to output JSON fields in a specific order. |

